- cs.DC (Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing) is the most likely category as the paper is about designing work-efficient parallel algorithms. 
- cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) is also likely as the paper discusses standard methods from fpt theory, such as kernelization and search trees. 
- cs.CC (Computational Complexity) is another possible category as the paper deals with fixed-parameter tractable (fpt) problems. 
- cs.DM (Discrete Mathematics) is a possible category as the paper discusses search trees and interleaving, which are related to combinatorial optimization. 
- cs.SY (Systems and Control) is a less likely category, but still possible as the paper deals with parallel algorithms and trade-offs between work efficiency and runtime improvements.
